    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the tip. i tried a bit of that but it's still acting weird and staying all greasy. what is the actual science behind why it separates like that? like why does the fat and the yolk not want to stay together?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hollandaise breaks when the emulsion collapses because the lecithin in the egg yolk can no longer hold the tiny fat droplets suspended in the water-based yolk mixture. This usually happens if the mixture gets too hot or if the butter is added too fast, overwhelming the yolk's ability to stabilize the fat. Once separated, separating butter you can try a cold water bath or adding a fresh yolk to re-stabilize the sauce by creating a new, stronger bond.",
      "source": "target",
